### 1.3 Domain Architecture Principles

#### 1.3.1 Bounded Context Isolation

```elixir
@domain_principles %{
  bounded_contexts: "Each domain encapsulates its own business logic",
  data_isolation: "Complete tenant data separation at all layers",
  loose_coupling: "Domains communicate via events and contracts",
  high_cohesion: "Related functionality grouped within domains",
  single_responsibility: "Each domain has one clear business purpose"
}
```

#### 1.3.2 Event-Driven Communication

```elixir
# Cross-domain communication pattern
defmodule Intelitor.Events.AlarmTriggered do
  use Ash.Notifier
  
  def notify(%{action: :trigger, resource: Intelitor.Alarms.AlarmEvent} = notification) do
    # Notify Video domain for recording
    # Notify Dispatch domain for response
    # Notify Communication domain for notifications
    Phoenix.PubSub.broadcast(
      Intelitor.PubSub,
      "alarms:#{notification.data.tenant_id}",
      {:alarm_triggered, notification.data}
    )
  end
end
```

### 1.4 Core Architectural Patterns

#### 1.4.1 Multi-Tenant Resource Pattern

```elixir
defmodule Intelitor.BaseResource do
  defmacro __using__(opts) do
    quote do
      use Ash.Resource,
        domain: unquote(opts[:domain]),
        data_layer: AshPostgres.DataLayer
      
      # Multi-tenancy enforced at resource level
      use Intelitor.Multitenancy.TenantResource
      
      # Common patterns
      attributes do
        uuid_primary_key :id
        timestamps()
      end
      
      policies do
        # Tenant isolation enforced
        bypass always() do
          authorize_if actor_attribute_equals(:role, "admin")
        end
      end
    end
  end
end
```

#### 1.4.2 Domain Service Pattern

```elixir
defmodule Intelitor.Alarms.Services.IncidentManagement do
  @moduledoc """
  Core business service for managing alarm incidents across domains
  """
  
  def create_incident(alarm, opts \\ []) do
    with {:ok, incident} <- create_alarm_record(alarm),
         :ok <- notify_dispatch_team(incident),
         :ok <- trigger_video_recording(incident),
         :ok <- log_audit_trail(incident) do
      {:ok, incident}
    end
  end
end
```

