## 4. API Architecture

### 4.1 Dual API Strategy

The system implements a comprehensive dual API approach to serve different client needs:

#### 4.1.1 GraphQL API

**Purpose**: Rich client applications, complex queries, real-time subscriptions  
**Capabilities**:

- Type-safe schema with full introspection
- Efficient data fetching with custom resolvers
- Real-time subscriptions via WebSocket
- Built-in caching and optimization

```elixir
defmodule IntelitorWeb.GraphQL.Schema do
  use Absinthe.Schema
  use AshGraphql, domains: [
    Intelitor.Core,
    Intelitor.Accounts,
    Intelitor.Alarms,
    Intelitor.Devices,
    # ... all 19 domains
  ]
  
  query do
    # Auto-generated queries for all resources
  end
  
  mutation do
    # Auto-generated mutations for all resources
  end
  
  subscription do
    field :alarm_triggered, :alarm_event do
      arg :tenant_id, non_null(:string)
      
      config fn args, _info ->
        {:ok, topic: "alarms:#{args.tenant_id}"}
      end
      
      trigger :trigger_alarm, topic: fn alarm ->
        "alarms:#{alarm.tenant_id}"
      end
    end
  end
end
```

#### 4.1.2 JSON:API

**Purpose**: Standard REST API, external integrations, mobile applications  
**Capabilities**:

- JSONAPI specification compliance
- Standardized error handling
- Filtering, sorting, and pagination
- Relationship inclusion

```elixir
defmodule IntelitorWeb.Router do
  use Phoenix.Router
  use AshJsonApi.Router,
    domains: [
      Intelitor.Core,
      Intelitor.Accounts,
      Intelitor.Alarms,
      # ... all domains
    ],
    open_api: "/api/docs"
  
  pipeline :api do
    plug :accepts, ["json"]
    plug IntelitorWeb.Plugs.AuthenticateAPI
    plug IntelitorWeb.Plugs.LoadTenant
  end
  
  scope "/api/v1" do
    pipe_through :api
    ash_json_api_routes()
  end
end
