## 9. Testing Architecture

### 9.1 Comprehensive Testing Strategy

#### 9.1.1 Test Pyramid Implementation

```text
                    ┌─────────────────┐
                    │   End-to-End    │ ← 5% (E2E Browser Tests)
                    └─────────────────┘
                ┌─────────────────────────┐
                │    Integration Tests    │ ← 15% (API & Cross-Domain)
                └─────────────────────────┘
        ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
        │           Unit Tests                │ ← 80% (Domain & Resource Tests)
        └─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

#### 9.1.2 Test Categories

**1. Unit Tests (80%)**:

- Domain resource tests (CRUD operations)
- Business logic validation
- Authorization and access control
- Multi-tenant isolation

**2. Integration Tests (15%)**:

- Cross-domain workflow testing
- API endpoint validation (GraphQL + JSON:API)
- Database transaction integrity
- Event propagation testing

**3. End-to-End Tests (5%)**:

- Complete user workflows via browser automation
- Real-time feature testing
- Security workflow validation
- Performance under load

#### 9.1.3 Multi-Tenant Testing Pattern

```elixir
defmodule Intelitor.Test.Support.TenantHelpers do
  def setup_tenant_context do
    tenant = insert(:tenant)
    organization = insert(:organization, tenant: tenant)
    user = insert(:user, tenant: tenant, organization: organization)
    
    %{tenant: tenant, organization: organization, user: user}
  end
  
  def with_tenant_context(test_context, fun) do
    Intelitor.Repo.put_tenant_id(test_context.tenant.id)
    
    try do
      fun.(test_context)
    after
      Intelitor.Repo.put_tenant_id(nil)
    end
  end
end

defmodule Intelitor.AlarmsTest do
  use Intelitor.DataCase
  import Intelitor.Test.Support.TenantHelpers
  
  describe "alarm triggering" do
    setup [:setup_tenant_context]
    
    test "triggers alarm and notifies appropriate domains", %{tenant: tenant} = context do
      with_tenant_context(context, fn _ctx ->
        device = insert(:device, tenant: tenant)
        
        {:ok, alarm} = Intelitor.Alarms.AlarmEvent.trigger(%{
          event_type: :motion,
          severity: :high,
          source_device_id: device.id
        })
        
        assert alarm.status == :new
        assert alarm.tenant_id == tenant.id
        
        # Verify cross-domain notifications were sent
        assert_received {:alarm_triggered, ^alarm}
      end)
    end
  end
end
```

